md:
giải nghĩa từ "enclosed" sang tiếng việt; đưa ra nghĩa tiếng việt theo từ loại và đưa ra câu ví dụ, các từ liên quan.

* Enclosed (verb) /ɪnˈkloʊzd/:
	+ Meaning: to surround or close something in on all sides
	+ Vietnamese: bao quanh, vây quanh
	+ Example sentence: The garden was enclosed by a high wall.
	+ Related words: surround, enclose, confine

* Enclosed (adjective) /ɪnˈkloʊzd/:
	+ Meaning: surrounded or closed in on all sides
	+ Vietnamese: được bao quanh, được vây quanh
	+ Example sentence: The enclosed area was reserved for VIP guests.
	+ Related words: surrounded, confined, restricted

Note: The verb "enclosed" can also mean to put something in a container or envelope, but this meaning is less common.
